LearnToHack static HTML and CSS cheatsheet
============================================

--------------
The HTML
--------------
<html></html> - Begins/ends the html code
<head></head> - Begins/ends the head aka "The stuff that effects the text."
<body></body> - Begins/ends the body aka "The text"
<title></title> - The title of the document (goes inside the head tag)
<h1><h2><h3> - Headers (The bigger the number, the smaller the text)
<p> - Paragraph tag
<br> - line break (aka returns to a new line)
<img src="ImageNameGoesHere.jpg"> - Image tag
<a href="www.websiteDomainGoesHere.com"> - Link tag
<div id="nameGoesHere" - div tag (aka organization tag)

--------------
The CSS
--------------
background-color: black; - Sets the background color to black
color: white; - sets the text color to white
text-align: center; - aligns the text to center
padding: 5px; - puts 5 pixles of space inbetween this div tag and any other 				div tag
line-height: 30px; - sets the height of the space inbetween lines of text 						vertically
height: 300px; - sets the height of the div element to 300px
width: 100px; - sets the width of the div element to 100px
float: left; - moves the div element over to the leftmost side of the screen
clear: both; - no text allowed on either side of the div tags above it
